 <h4>Answer the following questions to write a paragraph on ‘The historical 7th March Speech’. You should write it in about 250 words ᐅ</h4>
 <br><br>
 <h3><center>The historical 7th March Speech</center></h3>
 
 <p>The historical 7th March Speech of Sheikh Mujibur Rahman was a speech given by Sheikh Mujibur Rahman, a Bengali nationalist leader, on 7 March 1971. It was given at the Ramna Race Course in Dhaka to a gathering of over two million people during a period of escalating tensions between East Pakistan and the powerful political and military establishment of West Pakistan.On March 7, 1971, Bangabandhu Sheikh Mujibur Rahman called upon all Bangalees of then East Pakistan to launch a decisive struggle against the Pakistani occupation forces indicating for taking all-out preparations for the War of Liberation. On this day in 1971, Bangabandhu Mujib delivered his historic speech before several hundred thousands of people at the Suhrawardy Udyan in Dhaka.
 In a thunderous voice, Sheikh Mujib declared "This struggle is for our freedom, this struggle is for our independence", inspiring people from all walks of life to prepare for the war that the Pakistani regime would inflict upon the unarmed Bangalees 18 days later, committing one of the worst genocides in human history, when the Pakistan Army launched Operation Searchlight against Bengali civilians, intelligentsia, students, politicians, and armed personnel. So we remember The 7th march speech the key to success of liberation war.And we also sallot the father of Bangali nation for giving us freedom.</p>
